TITLE: Creating a Route Attribute Listener in Spiral Framework
DESCRIPTION: Example implementation of a TokenizationListenerInterface that collects route attributes from method annotations. The listener scans all classes, identifies methods with Route attributes, and registers them with the router.
SOURCE: https://github.com/spiral/docs/blob/3.14/docs/en/advanced/tokenizer.md#2025-04-20_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Spiral\Attributes\ReaderInterface;

final class RouteAttributeListener implements TokenizationListenerInterface
{
    private array $attributes = [];

    public function __construct(
        private readonly ReaderInterface $reader,
        private readonly RouterInterface $router
    ) {
    }

    public function listen(\ReflectionClass $class): void
    {
        foreach ($class->getMethods() as $method) {
            $route = $this->reader->firstFunctionMetadata($method, Route::class);

            if ($route === null) {
                continue;
            }

            $this->attributes[] = [$method, $route];
        }
    }

    public function finalize(): void
    {
        foreach ($this->attributes as [$method, $route]) {
            $this->router->addRoute(...);
        }
    }
}
```

