TITLE: Using a Filter in a Controller Method
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use a filter object in a controller method to handle user creation with validated input.
SOURCE: https://github.com/spiral/docs/blob/3.14/docs/en/cookbook/migration-from-v2.md#2025-04-20_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class UserController
{
    public function createUser(CreateUserFilter $filter): array
    {
        $user = new User(
            $filter->username,
            $filter->firstName,
            $filter->lastName
        );

        $user->setUtmData(
            $filter->utm->id,
            $filter->utm->source,
            ...
        );

