TITLE: Adding Method to PHP Class
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to add a method to a class with return type, parameters, visibility, final modifier, comments, and body.
SOURCE: https://github.com/spiral/docs/blob/3.14/docs/en/component/reactor.md#2025-04-20_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$class = new ClassDeclaration('MyClass');

$class->addMethod('ping')
    ->setPublic()
    ->setComment('My method')
    ->setReturnType('string')
    ->setReturnNullable()
    ->setFinal()
    ->setBody('return $a;')
    ->addAttribute('SomeAttribute')
        ->addParameter('a', null)
        ->setType('string')
        ->setNullable(true);

dump((string) $class);
```

